Technology Brief -- DNA Plant Technology Corp.:
   Genetically Altered Tomato
   Shows Resistance to Fungus
In effect, he said, the plants are getting an enhanced
immune system. The test data indicate "a significant
opportunity for extending the shelf life of fresh market
produce by increasing resistance to fungi which cause
post-harvest rot without the use of fungicides," said Dr.
Bedbrook. He said the genetically engineered varieties might
reach the market by the mid 1990s.
   DNA Plant Technology shares rose 50 cents to $8 in
national over-the-counter trading.